Learning Objectives
After the successful completion of this course, students will be able to . . .

Explain the problems of analyzing clustered data with multiple regression/ANOVA;
Identify the types of multilevel data structure in different research scenarios;
Describe the statistical and conceptual foundations of multilevel modeling;
Independently analyze real data using statistical software for multilevel modeling;
Evaluate published research that uses multilevel modeling;
Apply multilevel modeling in a research project, and effectively communicate findings/products in an oral research presentation or a written research report.

Prerequisite(s): PSYC 503: Regression and the General Linear Model (or a similar regression class)
Co-Requisite(s): None
Concurrent Enrollment: None
Recommended Preparation: Experience with statistical software (preferably R)

Communication
To promote independence and critical thinking, students are encouraged to work through the following process for obtaining answers to course-related questions before contacting the instructor:

consult the course syllabus;
consult a classmate;
post your questions on the Q&A channel on Slack;
meet with the instructor during office hours or Q&A sessions on Tuesdays;
for personal questions, email the instructor at hokchiol@usc.edu
